<br>
In Plane of Storms (gotcho flag, right?) there are some trees, lots of them.  This post however, is in regard to only one type, called A Wanton Tronera.  The trees are druids, and cast several spells.  The two most noteworthy to be aware of are &quot;Engorging Roots&quot; and &quot;Winged Death&quot;.  They hit like an Amtrak, so if you get rooted game's over.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
The basics are simple, pull up 61 air pet, bo4, muzzle, and a double dose of walnan loving.  Med to full, you'll likely need most of your mana if you're below 4k mana.  Find a Wantan (wonton?  no, it's different)  and get to work.  Kill a Wantan, gobble up your 7% aa solo (?!) and med up for the next kill.<br>
<br>
The basics, if it were only that, would make for a crowded zone full of mages.  The most difficult aspect of these battles are adds.  Nearly everything in PoS is indifferent, or at the least non kos except for the giants.  If, however, you're engaged on a mob then you'll find that all of the PoS inhabitants are dear friends and will help out in time of need.  If you get an add, please don't both hassling and trying to finish the tree, you will likely die.  So, prior to battle check in all directions to make sure you have no adds incoming.  The actual fight takes about 1-2 minutes, depending on crits and what not.  This is the spell cast order I use, test and let us know what works best for you:<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp annul<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp annul<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp malosini<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp fbot<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp fbot<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp fbot<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp char<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp (without resists, mob is usually about dead here.. may have to finish with another char, or fbot depending on resists)<br>
<br>
The reason I annul twice is I've been told they cast seasons on themselves, as well as possible DS and/or skin of some sort.  Since I'm not one to take a thrashing and find out for myself, I'll use the extra mana and play it safe.  <br>
<br>
As I stated earlier, these are 7-8% aa solo, and duo it's still 4% with both parties at 61%.  I haven't tested &quot;real&quot; exp solo, but it was 1% per kill duo'd.  I'd expect roughly the same solo.  I did also try to rain (sirocco) on these trees, but every wave was resisted even with malosini.  Someone with sunstorm wanna try and post results?<br>
<br>
There you have it, heaven in PoS.<br>
<br>
Toyorgrav - 61 mage<br>
